@startuml lock-contention
title Lock contention — fail-fast, queued grants, lease expiry
hide footbox
skinparam shadowing false

participant "Node A" as A
participant "Coordinator\n(all lock state lives here)" as C
participant "Node B" as B

== Fail-fast (default): contention is an error, never a silent wait ==

A -> C : LOCK [region 1]
C --> A : LOCK_GRANT [lease_ms]

B -> C : MEM_WRITE [ref in region 1][bytes]
C --> B : ERROR [LOCKED]
note right of B : module sees WASP_REMOTE_ELOCKED\n— retry or back off

B -> C : LOCK [region 1]
C --> B : ERROR [LOCKED]

A -> C : UNLOCK [region 1]
C --> A : MEM_ACK

B -> C : LOCK [region 1] (retry)
C --> B : LOCK_GRANT [lease_ms]

== Queued locks (coordinator policy — WaspNode(queue_locks=True)) ==

A -> C : LOCK [region 1]
C --> A : LOCK_GRANT [lease_ms]

B -> C : LOCK [region 1]
note over C
  Instead of failing fast, the coordinator
  **parks** B's request in the region's FIFO.
  B's executor just blocks on its RPC slot —
  the node needs no opinion, no protocol change.
  The wait is bounded (4 s < the node's 5 s
  RPC timeout), then ERROR [LOCKED] after all.
end note

A -> C : UNLOCK [region 1]
C --> A : MEM_ACK
C --> B : LOCK_GRANT [lease_ms]\n(sent the moment the region frees;\nthe lease clock starts **now**)
note right of B : zero wasted round-trips,\nFIFO fairness under contention

== Lease expiry: a dead node cannot deadlock the swarm ==

A -> C : LOCK [region 1]
C --> A : LOCK_GRANT [lease_ms = 5000]
A -> A : crashes / loses power\nstill "holding" the lock
...lease expires (5 s)...
B -> C : LOCK [region 1]
note over C : lease expired — the coordinator\nrevokes A's stale hold
C --> B : LOCK_GRANT [lease_ms]
@enduml
